│ only produce 'false' when both operands cannot make the min/max less-than     │
│ hold; if the other operand comparison (CmpYZ) is known, the transform should  │
│ fold into comparing Y vs Z rather than a blanket false. The function already  │
│ has a FoldIntoCmpYZ helper, but the else !IsSame branch unconditionally       │
│ returns false, ignoring the available Y vs Z knowledge.\n\nGiven the specific │
│ setup (samesign ult, umax), when CmpXZ is false (X >= Z), the correct         │
